  <!-- ═══ KEY METRICS ═══ -->
  <h2>The Methodology & Assumptions</h2>
  <p>To value Micron, we use a two-stage Discounted Cash Flow (DCF) model. First, we project Free Cash Flow (FCF) for the next 5 years (the high-growth phase). Second, we calculate a Terminal Value to represent all cash flows beyond year 5. Finally, we discount everything back to today's dollars, add net cash, and divide by shares outstanding.</p>

  <div class="assumption-grid">
    <div class="assump-card">
      <div class="ac-title">Years 1-5 FCF Growth</div>
      <div class="ac-value">{(growthRatePhase1 * 100).toFixed(0)}%</div>
      <div class="ac-desc">Micron is riding the massive AI tailwind (HBM demand). We project 18% annualized FCF growth over the next five years, capturing peak cycle earnings before a potential moderation.</div>
